# Steps Layer Rules — "Validate and Flow"

You are editing a **Step** file. Steps are "smart" — they contain ALL business
logic AND all assertions. Page Objects are "dumb" (locators + getters only).

## Pattern to Follow

```javascript
const { BaseSteps } = require('../base.steps');  // adjust depth
const { FeatureModal } = require('../../pages/{module}/modals/{feature}.modal');

class FeatureSteps extends BaseSteps {
  constructor(page) {
    super(page);
    this.modal = new FeatureModal(page);
  }

  async fillForm({ field1, field2 }) {
    if (field1) await this.clearAndFill(this.modal.field1Input, field1);
    if (field2) await this.selectFromDropdown(this.modal.field2Selector, field2);
  }

  async submit() {
    await this.modal.submitButton.click();
    await this.waitForPageReady();
  }

  async verifyFieldError(expectedMessage) {
    await this.verifyErrorMessage(this.modal.fieldError, expectedMessage);
  }
}

module.exports = { FeatureSteps };
```

## Available BaseSteps Helpers — USE THESE
- `this.waitForPageReady()` — after navigation/submission
- `this.waitForNetworkIdle(timeout)` — after API calls
- `this.smartWait()` — wait for spinners/skeletons to disappear (catches timeouts gracefully)
- `this.waitForStable(locator)` — wait for element to stop re-rendering
- `this.verifyElementsVisible(...locators)` — smoke checks
- `this.verifyInputText(locator, expected)` — text content assertions
- `this.verifyInputValue(locator, expected)` — input value assertions
- `this.selectFromDropdown(trigger, optionText)` — dropdown selection
- `this.selectRandomFromDropdown(trigger, options)` — random dropdown
- `this.clearAndFill(locator, value)` — clear + fill input
- `this.clearInputField(locator)` — clear + Tab for validation tests
- `this.verifyErrorMessage(locator, expected)` — error assertions
- `this.verifyButtonState(locator, enabled)` — button state checks

## STRICT RULES
- Every class extends `BaseSteps`
- Page Objects instantiated in constructor
- ALL assertions (expect, verify*) live here — NEVER in Page Objects
- Method names = user intent (e.g., `createExpense`, NOT `clickButtonAndFillForm`)
- NO hardcoded selectors — always reference `this.pageObject.locatorName`
- NO `page.locator()` calls — all locators come from Page Objects
- NEVER use `page.waitForTimeout()` — use `waitForPageReady()` or `smartWait()` instead
- **CAUTION with `waitForPageReady()`** in SPA/micro-frontend apps — it uses `networkidle` which can hang. Prefer `smartWait()` which catches the timeout.
- ALWAYS export: `module.exports = { ClassName }`
